1. Sort the `products` lexicographically.
2. Initialize an empty result list and an empty `currentPrefix` string.
3. Iterate through each letter of `searchWord`, appending the letter to `currentPrefix`.
4. Use a binary search to find the starting position of the suggested products with the common prefix `currentPrefix`.
5. Initialize an empty suggestions list.
6. Iterate from the starting position and add at most 3 product names to the suggestions list that have the common prefix with `currentPrefix`. Stop adding product names either when there are no more products with the common prefix or 3 suggestions are added.
7. Add the suggestions list to the result list.
8. Return the result list after iterating through all the characters of `searchWord`.
